<br>
1) raise the level of the pet (53-55?);<br>
2) increase the pet's maximum damage (by 15-20?);<br>
3) increase the pet's dexterity (this would increase all procs, including flurry) by 100;<br>
4) be undispellable.<br>
<br>
The pet needs to do about 85 DPS to do 15k damage in 3 minutes.  In other words, he needs to be *almost* as good as a 60 warrior.<br>
<br>
Please note that with this skill, the pet would still do less damage than warriors, monks, and rogues during the same time frame: hardly unbalancing.<br>
<br>
Utuno, Arch Mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umagesoltari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mage Soltari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/02 10:10:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cs.vu.nl/~dhbergen/gohansmall.gif width=100 height=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmmm</span><hr size=1> Sounds nice ... wuld be nice little show. Keep in mind though, that the 13k+ nukes are CRITICAL hits of Manaburn, usually it does anywhere from 600-8k damage, non-crit. Seeing as Frenzied BO would be the same effect every time by your design, I don't think it should get to do 13k damage in those three minutes. Don't get me wrong, I would jump with joy if they did cause it would make me kick ass, a lot, but I don't see it as something that might happen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><TABLE bgcolor = black border=3>
